main event: A civilian observer reported sighting a white star-like light over the Wright-Patterson area in Dayton, Ohio on August 29, 1968.
interesting points: The object appeared to be moving very rapidly across the sky.
The observer could not determine the distance or size of the object.
The description was consistent with a previous sighting report, but the data was insufficient for full evaluation.
The observer was requested to complete a detailed form but did not return it within 30 days.
No photographs or physical evidence were obtained.
